class:: NdMNameSpace
categories:: NdM
summary:: Global registry for NdM instances, argument buses, and tags.

DESCRIPTION::
NdMNameSpace is the global registry that stores all NdM-related bookkeeping
independent of any particular NdMSpace instance.

It manages:
list::
## Key â†’ NdM instance mappings
## Argument-bus allocation and history
## Tag registration and lookup
## Restore helpers used after graph rebuild or environment switches
::

NdMSpace and helper classes such as NdMTag delegate all namespace-level
lookup and persistence tasks to NdMNameSpace.
Users normally do not instantiate or manipulate this class directly.

CLASSMETHODS::

method:: acquire
Return the singleton NdMNameSpace instance.
returns:: NdMNameSpace
discussion::
All namespace access goes through this singleton.

method:: reset
Clear all stored keys, buses, and tags.
returns:: nil
discussion::
This is typically triggered indirectly via NdMSpace.clean or reset.

method:: nodesForTag
Return all NdM instances associated with the given tag.
argument:: tagSymbol
Tag symbol.
returns:: Array

method:: allTags
Return a list of all registered tag symbols.
returns:: Array

method:: restoreFromNode
Restore namespace state from an existing server node.
argument:: node
Server node reference.
returns:: nil
discussion::
Used internally during graph rebuild or space restoration.
Not intended for direct user invocation.